				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Matching Adventures: The Werewolf&#039;s Treasure" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>You are a treasure hunter and you enter the deep forests that surround a small town. You hear about the legend of the pure gold coins that are hidden there. According to villagers, these are guarded by a creature of the night, a big werewolf. You should look for coins and be alert for threats, get objects to advance in the search and hopefully catch the werewolf ... If he does not catch you first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;About the game:&amp;#10;It is a card game in the style of &amp;quot;Memory Game&amp;quot; for 1 to 4 players.&amp;#10;The main objective is to find the 6 Gold coins that will be hidden among the game's deck.&amp;#10;Along the same we will be stalked by the Werewolf, the protector of the coins that will try to eliminate you, to avoid it we must find 4 objects: Wolf Trap, Rope, Shotgun and Cartridges.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game play:&amp;#10;Four cards are placed in a row and face down, one after another in 3 columns, thus completing some 12 cards (4x3). For each turn, the player must turn (reveal) 2 cards from among these 12. If the 2 cards we reveal are not from the same object, we place these cards face down in the same place. Otherwise, if these 2 cards are of the same object, we can obtain one of those cards and the other is placed in the discard deck; that is, we now have that object in our inventory to use. Once this situation has happened, we must replace the two cards that we took from the playing field (the 12 cards) with another 2 cards that we are going to draw from the game deck; there always have to be 12 cards on the table. Once the turn is over, we repeat revealing another 2 cards and so on until we get all the coins or be eliminated by the wolves. When we reveal 1 coin, it becomes part of our inventory and we start a new shift, that is, it is not necessary to reveal 2 coins to obtain it. In the same way we must replace 1 card to take its place in the field of play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
